<h2>Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies</h2>

<div>
	<h3>Ingredients</h3>

	<ul>
		<li>250g plain flour</li>
		<li>1/2 teaspoon bicarbonate of soda</li>
		<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
		<li>170g unsalted butter, melted</li>
		<li>200g dark brown soft sugar</li>
		<li>100g caster sugar</li>
		<li>1 tablespoon vanilla extract</li>
		<li>1 egg</li>
		<li>1 egg yolk</li>
		<li>325g chocolate chips</li>
	</ul>
</div>

<div>
	<h3>Method</h3>

	<ul>
		<li>Preheat the oven to 170 C / Gas mark 3</li>
		<li>Grease baking trays or line with parchment</li>
		<li>Sift together the flour, bicarb and salt; set aside</li>
		<li>In a medium bowl, cream together the melted butter, brown sugar and caster sugar until well blended</li>
		<li>Beat in the vanilla, egg and egg yolk until light and creamy</li>
		<li>Mix in the sifted ingredients until just blended</li>
		<li>Stir in the chocolate chips by hand using a wooden spoon</li>
		<li>Drop cookie dough onto the prepared baking trays, with each cookie around 4 tablespoons of dough (for smaller cookies, drop 1 rounded tablespoonful and adjust baking time as necessary). Do not flatten the dough. Cookies should be about 8cm apart.</li>
		<li>Bake for 15 to 17 minutes in the preheated oven, or until the edges are lightly toasted</li>
		<li>Cool on baking trays for a few minutes before transferring to wire racks to cool completely</li>
	</ul>
</div>

Link to this recipe: http://jsrn.net/tablecloth/#baking/chewy_chocolate_chip_cookies